explanation: The solution uses a priority queue to store the differences between corresponding elements in the two arrays, along with their indices. It iteratively reduces the largest differences by 1, updating the result and pushing the new differences back into the priority queue, until it has used up all available modifications or the priority queue is empty. This greedy approach ensures that the sum of squared differences is minimized.

